definition: race/nationality/ethnicity/clan/by extension, social group (e.g. office workers 上班族)

sentences.english: Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah, Jedaiah. These were the heads of the priests and of their kinsmen in the days of Jeshua.
sentences.chinese: 这些人是耶叔亚时期中的司祭，和他们兄弟的族长。

sentences.english: These are the dukes of Edom.
All these were heads of families, chiefs as listed in their genealogy, and they lived in Jerusalem.
sentences.chinese: 这些人都是着名的族长，住在耶路撒冷。

sentences.english: A Jutish chief became the King of Kent in 449.
sentences.chinese: 449年，一位朱特族长成为了肯特的国王。

sentences.english: These were the heads of the families of Ladan.
The men listed above by name were leaders of their clans. Their families increased greatly
sentences.chinese: 以上所记的人名都是作族长的，他们宗族的人数增多。

sentences.english: Of the sons of Elizaphan; Shemaiah the chief, and his brethren two hundred
sentences.chinese: 以利撒反子孙中有族长示玛雅和他的弟兄二百人。

sentences.english: To be blunt, El the patriarchs seem to have worshiped the Canaanite God, El.
sentences.chinese: 大胆地说，族长们似乎曾经崇拜迦南的上帝。

sentences.english: Old clan long eye a black almost fall down.
sentences.chinese: 老族长眼一黑差点栽倒。

sentences.english: These chief fathers of the Levites were chief throughout their generations; these dwelt at Jerusalem.
sentences.chinese: 以上都是利未人著名的族长住在耶路撒冷。

sentences.english: The land never belongs to the patriarchs to whom it was promised.
sentences.chinese: 上帝曾许诺于族长，可土地却从未，属于他们。

sentences.english: Of the sons of Gershom; Joel the chief, and his brethren an hundred and thirty
sentences.chinese: 革顺子孙中有族长约珥和他的弟兄一百三十人。

sentences.english: And Zadok, a young man mighty of valour, and of his father's house twenty and two captains.
sentences.chinese: 还有少年大能的勇士撒督，同着他的有族长二十二人。

sentences.english: Zadok, a young man mighty in valor, and twenty-two commanders from his own fathers' house.
sentences.chinese: 还有少年大能的勇士撒督，同著他的有族长二十二人。

sentences.english: And David got together the sons of Aaron, and the Levites;
sentences.chinese: 哥辖子孙中有族长乌列和他的弟兄一百二十人。
